race.comment: Tricky race to assess with a few of these at the races for the first time. Of the raced brigade KHOIRGIRL (4) is unlucky to still be a maiden finishing runner-up in both starts to date and strikes a winnable contest here. Butler sticks in the saddle following the past two outings and can go one better against this lot. JUCASI (1) placed around this circuit when resuming and will have come on with that run now under the belt. Top-three credentials at odds. SWAGGERING (3) best of the rest with the claim from the inside alley. ANCIENT SCENT (6) was safely held on debut but still ran well when finishing second and has to be kept safe fresh with Maloney booked.
